JP Morgan Fund Manager Calls Nokia Good Bet, Kauppalehti Says

-- B y   D i a n a   b e n - A a r o n
-- 
2011-03-01T09:42:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/jp-morgan-fund-manager-calls-nokia-good-bet-kauppalehti-says.html
  Nokia Oyj  shares are likely to gain
in the next three years, Patrick Vermeulen, a  fund manager  at JP
Morgan Asset Management, said according to the Finnish business
daily Kauppalehti.  “Nokia is currently an indisputably cheap share, but the
company’s turn for the better will take time,” Vermeulen said
according to the newspaper. Nokia Chief Executive Officer
Stephen Elop is taking the company in the right direction in
adopting smartphone software from Microsoft Corp., the newspaper
cited him as saying.  Click here for web link in Finnish  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
